RELEASE INFORMATION

Project:           HW Probe
Version:           1.3
Date:              November 26, 2017


This file explains how to install and setup environment
for the tool in your computer.


Content:

   1. Requirements for Linux
   2. Configure and Install
   3. Usage
   4. Live ISO
   5. Docker


1. REQUIREMENTS FOR LINUX
=========================

   1. Perl 5
   2. hwinfo
   3. curl
   4. dmidecode
   5. pciutils
   6. usbutils

1.1 Suggestions

   1. smartmontools
   2. systemd-tools
   3. hdparm
   4. sysstat
   5. memtester
   6. inxi
   7. edid-decode
   8. rfkill
   9. xinput
   10. i2c-tools
   11. hplip
   12. pnputils
   13. acpica



2. CONFIGURE AND INSTALL
========================

   This command will install a hw-probe program in the
   PREFIX/bin system directory:

     sudo make install prefix=PREFIX [/usr, /usr/local, ...]

2.1 Remove

     sudo make uninstall prefix=PREFIX



3. USAGE
========

   Make a probe and upload result to the DB (run as root,
   PC_NAME â€” any name of the computer):

     hw-probe -all -upload -id PC_NAME



4. LIVE ISO
===========

   The Live ISO with hw-probe installed: https://mirror.yandex.ru/rosa/rosa2016.1/iso/ROSA.Fresh.R9/
   
   Boot this Linux ISO in Live mode on your computer and make a probe (see USAGE).



5. DOCKER
=========

   You can easily make a probe on any Linux distribution
   without installing the tool with the help of the Docker image:
   
      docker pull linuxhw/hw-probe
      docker run -it -v /dev:/dev:ro -v /lib/modules:/lib/modules:ro -v /etc/os-release:/etc/os-release:ro -v /var/log:/var/log:ro --privileged --net=host --pid=host linuxhw/hw-probe -all -upload -id PC_NAME
     
      You may need to run 'xhost +local:' before docker run to collect X11 info (xrandr, xinput, etc.).



Enjoy!
